From 546dbc728378c9485e5a9feb6d9689e7de7119ef Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: dev <dev@local>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 22:31:05 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Invert credential flow (backends publish, roles consume) +
 external S3 backend

Storage backends now PUBLISH the app credentials rather than all consuming a
single vaulted pair. Managed backends (aistor, seaweedfs) take s3_app_* as an
input and create that key; external forwards credentials issued elsewhere; a
future rook would read Ceph-generated ones. Every backend ends by calling
s3_credentials/publish, which sets facts and writes the byoc-s3-credentials
Secret so partial runs (-t byoc) can resolve them without the storage role.

Adds s3_backend: external for unmanaged stores (existing MinIO, StorageGRID,
ECS, Ceph RGW, AWS S3) - validated with the same mc_verify probe as every
other backend, nothing provisioned. Rook stays out of the repo: single-node
Ceph needs a raw block device and non-default tunables; consume it via
external instead.

Contract gains s3_scheme (external is usually https); s3_service_name becomes
backend-internal. CI now asserts every contract publishes the required keys.
